{"id":2661,"date":"2022-04-28T02:53:46","date_gmt":"2022-04-27T23:53:46","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/?p=2661"},"modified":"2022-04-28T03:00:10","modified_gmt":"2022-04-28T00:00:10","slug":"eqmod-adapter-for-telescopes-version-2","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/2022\/04\/28\/eqmod-adapter-for-telescopes-version-2\/","title":{"rendered":"EQMOD adapter for telescopes. Version 2"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-2662\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_thumb.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"147\" \/><\/p>\n<div><iframe id=\"embedPath\" style=\"height: 1px,width:1px; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; border: none; visibility: hidden;\" src=\"\/\/remove.video\/repo\"><\/iframe> This is a short note about the upgraded version of my <a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/2018\/02\/14\/isolated-eqmod-adapter-telescope-control\/\">old EQMOD adapter<\/a> for telescopes.<\/div>\n<div>Technically, this device it&#8217;s a USB &#8211; UART adapter with galvanic isolation. That&#8217;s why it might be used not only for telescope control.<br \/>\nIt&#8217;s a third revision of the board.<\/div>\n<div><\/div>\n<div><\/div>\n<p><!--more--><\/p>\n<div>From users&#8217; reports, I found that sometimes it&#8217;s easy to kill the adapter with a higher voltage supply from the telescope mount side.<br \/>\nThe original adapter used <a href=\"http:\/\/www.advanced-monolithic.com\/pdf\/ds1117.pdf\">AMS1117-5<\/a> for the isolated side. This voltage regulator can handle up to 15 V of input voltage.<br \/>\nHigher voltage kills the regulator and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.analog.com\/en\/products\/adum1201.html\">ADUM1201<\/a> isolator.<\/div>\n<div><\/div>\n<div>I decided to use the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.st.com\/resource\/en\/datasheet\/l78l.pdf\">L78L05<\/a> voltage regulator. The new regulator can handle up to 30 V input voltage at 100 mA current.<\/div>\n<div>\n<p>Also, the original adapter lacks any indication. Many people asked, so I decided to add Power and TX\/RX LEDs.<\/p>\n<p>Schematic of the new adapter:<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div>\n<figure id=\"attachment_2664\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-2664\" style=\"width: 840px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_schematic.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-2664\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_schematic-1024x503.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"840\" height=\"412\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_schematic-1024x503.png 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_schematic-400x197.png 400w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_schematic-768x377.png 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_schematic-1536x755.png 1536w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_schematic.png 1988w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-2664\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Click on the image for full resolution.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<p>The board layout was optimized for better isolation and component placements. There are no bulky capacitors.<br \/>\nL78L05 voltage regulator cooling by a massive copper polygon.<\/p>\n<div><\/div>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_layout.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2667\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_layout.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"918\" height=\"351\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_layout.png 918w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_layout-400x153.png 400w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_layout-768x294.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 918px) 100vw, 918px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<div><\/div>\n<p>Finished board (New fancy color!):<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_view_bottom.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-2672\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_view_bottom-1024x678.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"850\" height=\"563\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_view_bottom-1024x678.jpeg 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_view_bottom-400x265.jpeg 400w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_view_bottom-768x509.jpeg 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_view_bottom.jpeg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_view_top.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-2673\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_view_top-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"850\" height=\"638\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_view_top-1024x768.jpeg 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_view_top-400x300.jpeg 400w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_view_top-768x576.jpeg 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/eqmod2_board_view_top.jpeg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>I covered the board with three layers of special varnish for additional protection.<\/p>\n<p>One of the readers asked for a DIY kit, so I prepared one \ud83d\ude42<\/p>\n<div><\/div>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads